headline: Maker of Folgers Brews Tariff Relief for Coffee Drinkers
summary: J.M. Smucker said Tuesday that it is no longer considering raising prices on its supermarket coffee this winter, after the Trump administration rolled back tariffs on coffee and dozens of other foodstuffs and agricultural goods.  Smucker, which owns brands such as Folgers and Café Bustelo, had already raised coffee prices twice this year.  The Orrville, Ohio-based company said in August that it was likely to do so again this winter, as costs to import coffee beans increased further.

headline: Smucker: Fiscal Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: ORRVILLE, Ohio (AP) — J.M. Smucker Co. (SJM) on Tuesday reported fiscal second-quarter earnings of $241.3 million. On a per-share basis, the Orrville, Ohio-based company said it had profit of $2.26. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were $2.10 per share.

headline: The J.M. Smucker Co. Announces Fiscal 2026 Second Quarter Results
summary: The J.M. Smucker Co. (NYSE: SJM) today announced results for the second quarter ended October 31, 2025, of its 2026 fiscal year. Financial results for the second quarter of fiscal year 2026 reflect the divestiture of certain Sweet Baked Snacks value brands on March 3, 2025, and the divestiture of the Voortman® business on December 2, 2024. All comparisons are to the second quarter of the prior fiscal year, unless otherwise noted.
